  "pk": 2,
  "fields": {
    "name": "Bolognese Fishing",
    "slug": "bolognese-fishing",
    "description": "Bolognese fishing is a popular fishing method, especially for catching carp, bream, crucian carp and other freshwater fish, and is mainly practiced on rivers. Its name comes from the Italian city of Bologna, where it was first developed. \r\nThis fishing method involves the use of a long, flexible fishing line, called a bolognese, which is equipped with a reel, a float and a hook or set of hooks. The line is usually between 4 and 8 meters long and is designed to evenly distribute the weight of the fish…",
